(firstQuint)Migraine Study in Adolescent Patients.

 The purpose of this study is to determine whether the combination product, sumatriptan and naproxen sodium, is effective compared to placebo in the treatment of acute migraine in adolescent subjects 12-17 years old.

 Subjects will treat two migraine attacks over a ~25 week period.

